      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;assignment-3-inheritance&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Assignment 3: inheritance&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#assignment-3-inheritance&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-1-colored-lists&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Exercise 1: colored lists&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#exercise-1-colored-lists&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We consider lists that:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;consist of green and red nodes, where&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;each node is labeled with an integer, and&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;the head node is green.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We model such lists with the following classes and interfaces:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://unibz-oofp-25-26.github.io/img/diagrams/plantuml/ass3_ex1.svg&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;book-hint warning&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Restriction.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;You can assume that lists are acyclic, i.e. no node points to one of its ancestors.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Complete or modify the abstract class &lt;code&gt;AbstractNode&lt;/code&gt; and the classes &lt;code&gt;RedNode&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;GreenNode&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;HeadNodeImpl&lt;/code&gt; in the folder &lt;code&gt;ex1&lt;/code&gt;, so that:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
